The `URI is not hierarchical` occurs because the URI for a resource within a jar file is going to look something like this: `file:/example.jar!/file.txt`. You cannot read the entries within a `jar` (a `zip` file) like it was a plain old [File](http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/io/File.html).

